Teaching Practice is carried out in accordance with oral or written agreement, either  in the form of teaching assistance (in the University) or in preparation and/or implementation of staff training in the external organization.  In the agreement the supervisor(s) are identified as well as the details of their feedback delivery.
Practical assignments include the preparation and implementation of study material or parts of them, the self-reflection and report, and responding to the feedback from the supervisor(s). The supervisor(s) will provide feedback on how the student performed the tasks and her development process.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide knowledge and experience of adult teaching. To apply the knowledge and skills acquired during the academic research or a certain course in a didactic context. To develop the skills of preparing study materials, argumenting and active listening.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the MA student has some knowledge and skills of adult teaching. The MA student is able analyze analytically and systematically the particular phenomena related to the change processes in society. She is able to run the seminar, prepare study texts and assignments, and evaluate the learners' independent work.
